I guess the guy I met on the street on the way to the restaurant should have been an omen. I was a block away from Bobby Van's and lost my bearings. PS, no cars are allowed in the area. When I asked him for directions, he happily pointed me in the right direction but warned be it "wasn't  very good". First off, the service for our large party of 20, was abysmal. It took over 45 minutes to serve us. The first ones served were finished eating, before the last were served. This was probablyy because they only assigned one waiter to handle our entire table. They brought us out warm plates for the steak but by the time the steak came, the plates were cold.  The last two served, received the following comment from the waiter "you asked for medium well, it takes longer to cook". Yeah, but not 45 minutes. As far as the food, slightly below what you would expect from a top NYC steakhouse. The Porterhouse was cooked perfectly but a little short on flavor. The creamed spinach wasn't creamed. The sweet potato fries were excellent, however, the couple sitting next to us were eating regular fries and complaining about how salty they were. I would say all in all, a solid 3, maybe 3.5.

Nothing was cooked to the right temperature, as it was severely undercooked. The steaks do not come with a side so we had to order that separately and that was $10-12ea. It was served at room temperature. We went through the wine list and ordered several bottles that were no longer available. The steaks were tender and seasoned well and the wine we received was decent(Flora Springs Merlot 2016). It would have been lovely if there was a decanter and had a chance to breath. After our meal we were not offered any dessert or after dinner drinks so we opted to leave. Our bill was $391. I have been going there for years, personal, business, and even had a "major birthday" bash with 30 people there. It is normally a 5 star experience, but I was there last night with a friend and unfortunately they are slipping a bit. Don't get me wrong, still great food and very good service, just not the meticulous outstanding service I've experienced in the past. It's the attention to detail that separate the good from the outstanding, which should be standard in an upper end steak house. Just a few examples: the bartender had no idea how to make a sour (and when I finally did finish my pseudo sour and ordered a glass of wine, the empty glass was still on the table as we were moving on to dessert); the sides were left on the table and not plated; we asked for steak sauce and got a bottle of A-1. I asked the server, "Didn't you used to have your own Bobby Van's sauce?" and he returned with a small cup that we carefully rationed; we had to ask for a water refill each time we finished (which I will say the waiter promptly provided, but really, should you have to ask ...?) and we felt a bit rushed as we were winding down. Will I return? Yes. But, please, they need to get back to the first class service that has been their staple.
